Hey everybody! Posted this last week but due to a lack of response I'll post again. I'm looking for an Android developer to join our company Amsterdam. If you're interested or just want to know more, shoot me a message and we can meet up for a cup of coffee :slightly_smiling_face: :thumbsup: 

<https://im-in.homerun.co/android-developer>

Good morning all. I work for a startup called Worklily that just launched. Worklily is a tech freelance platform dedicated to connecting companies with top-level tech talent for short-term projects. We want top-quality talent and have a minimum hourly rate in place so you aren't being undercut by other freelancers low balling their worth. Furthermore, we match you with projects so no more searching for projects and applying and competing with numerous others.

Seeking Android and other mobile app devs on our platform - apply today and use referral code WLILY16 to get an extra $50 on top of the first project you complete. Questions? Message me! Thanks.

<http://worklily.com/instantApply>

By the way, right now we are only open to Canada for the beta, but will expand to the US and other countries soon. If you are outside Canada, you can join the waitlist by filling out this form: <http://eepurl.com/cjPgg1>

EDIT: And we also have a Slack group for tech freelancers you can join, open to all - <https://worklily.typeform.com/to/yQ73Lc>
